<p>Our seven largest non-financial units — Buffalo News, Fechheimer, Kirby, Nebraska Furniture Mart, Scott Fetzer Manufacturing Group, See's Candies, and World Book — had combined operating earnings before interest and taxes of $180 million. Their net interest expense was only $2 million. Thus, pre-tax earnings on the equity capital employed amounted to $178 million on equity of only $175 million. If these seven business units had operated as a single company, their after-tax earnings would have been approximately $100 million — a return of about 57% on equity capital.</p>



